Issue #65 delegated Engram setup adjudication

The cutover harness reached a fully installed, healthy Packy state, then stopped
at 2026-07-18T14:36:33Z because its first final gate byte-compared the complete
Codex config across Packy's explicit `engram setup codex` delegation.

The following two diagnostic reruns were executed after that stop to determine
whether the digest change represented contributor loss. They touched only the
Engram-owned Codex setup surface. Their complete output was identical and is
recorded below. Inspection showed Codex reserialized tilde paths to absolute
paths and Engram refreshed `marketplaces.engram.last_updated`; contributor
sections, normalized Packy-external surfaces, the Engram binary, and runtime
remained present.

2026-07-18T14:40:33Z
command=/opt/homebrew/bin/engram setup codex
config_sha256_before=4779f5e3d150a2206a76afc0feb46e4beb850ee0c388102fcca7fa8b31790f36
config_sha256_after=d226c5d4485fbff8ad5eb6675806df7a0bf427b9343bd4eb042b4a1889f51b8d
exit_status=0
output:
✓ Installed codex plugin (3 files)
  → /Users/argote/.codex

Next steps:
  1. Restart Codex so MCP config and plugin are reloaded
  2. Verify ~/.codex/config.toml has [mcp_servers.engram]
  3. Verify model_instructions_file + experimental_compact_prompt_file are set
  4. Verify plugin is installed with: codex plugin list
  5. If codex CLI was absent during setup, install manually: codex plugin marketplace add Gentleman-Programming/engram --ref main && codex plugin add engram@engram

